main event: On 11 October 1951, multiple unidentified flying objects were observed in the skies over Minneapolis, Minnesota, moving at high speeds with erratic flight patterns.
interesting points: The objects were reported to glow and display rays of color without visible vapor trails., Observers described the shapes as multiple and distinctly controlled in flight., There were credible witnesses including pilots and ground observers confirming the sighting., The sighting lasted approximately 5 minutes, and the objects changed directions rapidly., The investigation concluded with uncertainty, listing possible explanations like balloons or aircraft, but no definitive identification was made.
